{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W1UqmjC5DfwRNS8rCMs1AE","type":"tool_result","content":"A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\nEach member is exposed via NodePort with external hostnames:\n\n- domain-rs-1:31181\n- domain-rs-2:31182\n- domain-rs-3:31183\n\nA mongo-client pod is available with those hostnames mapped to a node IP.\n\nTask:\n- Configure the replica set to advertise the external endpoints (split-horizon).\n- Do not change the NodePort services.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n mongodb get pod mongo-rs-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n0\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ /bin/sh -c '\nkubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n'\n\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl create namespace mongodb\nnamespace/mongodb created\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/services.yaml\nservice/mongo created\nservice/mongo-external-0 created\nservice/mongo-external-1 created\nservice/mongo-external-2 created\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/statefulset.yaml\nstatefulset.apps/mongo-rs created\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ for i in $(seq 1 60); do\n  ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts mongo-rs -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n  if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  sleep 5\ndone\nexit 1\n\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\nrs.initiate({_id:\"rs0\",members:[\n  {_id:0,host:\"mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n  {_id:1,host:\"mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n  {_id:2,host:\"mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n]})'\n\n{ ok: 1 }\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n  kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n  sleep 3\ndone\nexit 1\n\ntrue\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\" \"}{range .status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")]}{.address}{\"\\n\"}{end}{end}' | awk '$1 !~ /control-plane|master/ {print $2; exit}')\nif [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n  # Single-node cluster (only the control-plane node, e.g. default\n  # kind): fall back to its InternalIP instead of failing.\n  node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")].address}')\nfi\nif [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n  exit 1\nfi\ncat <<EOF | kubectl -n mongodb apply -f -\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: mongo-client\nspec:\n  restartPolicy: Never\n  hostAliases:\n  - ip: \"$node_ip\"\n    hostnames:\n    - domain-rs-1\n    - domain-rs-2\n    - domain-rs-3\n  containers:\n  - name: mongosh\n    image: mongo:6.0\n    command: [\"sleep\", \"3600\"]\nEOF\n\npod/mongo-client created\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod mongo-client --timeout=300s\npod/mongo-client condition met\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':verify] $ kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n4\n\n[precondition:external_access_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'external_access_fixture':probe] $ kubectl -n mongodb get svc mongo-external-1\nNAME               